<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/997: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-27T23:00:00-03:00">August 27, 1935—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 28—6:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>202. My 200, August 27, 6 p.m. Foreign Minister tells me he had a long
                            discussion with the President and gave him our ideas in full. The
                            President was much impressed and promised to take all possible measures
                            to ensure early ratification.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>